strong>Chris has a special interest in the treatment of Male Fertility and General Health, Digestive problems, Sports injuries &amp; Chronic Pain Disorders.</strong></h3>\r\n<strong> </strong>\r\n\r\nDr Eddy applies extensive knowledge of anatomy and physiology by effectively integrating it into his practice of Natural Medicine. Different modalities are combined including Acupuncture, Herbal Medicine, Nutrition &amp; Massage Therapy in order to provide for you a safe, effective and natural treatment, healing both the mind and body.Â  It is ensured that our Patients are active participants in their own good health and that together they work out a treatment plan that provides the best possible outcome.\r\n<strong> </strong>\r\n<h3><strong>Therapy</strong></h3>\r\nChris practices traditional Chinese medicine which includes therapies of acupuncture, cupping, herbal medicine and massage. Chinese medicine treats a very wide range of ailments; however a lot of Chrisâ€™s time is focused on treating male health &amp; fertility, chronic pain and digestive disorders.\r\nJapanese and Chinese Style Acupuncture\r\n\r\nAcupuncture does not need to be painful to be effective. Dr Eddy has studied various styles of acupuncture including Chinese, Japanese and more western approaches, with the aim to offer his patients the best therapeutic outcome. The Japanese style uses disposable needles of very fine gauge, which means little or no pain upon insertion.\r\n<h3>Chinese Herbal Medicine</h3>\r\nDr Eddy tailors each formula specifically to his patientsâ€™ individual health and lifestyle needs. Some raw herb formulas may not have the best taste, but they have been proven over thousands of years to help our bodies heal themselves. Dr Eddy often offers his patientsâ€™ a choice of raw &amp; granulated herbs as an integral part of their treatment. Sometimes herbal pills are prescribed in conjunction with the patient\'s raw herbs when traveling or boiling preparation may be inconvenient.\r\n<h3><strong>Cupping</strong></h3>\r\nDr Eddy has used Cupping Therapy effectively to help heal chronically sore muscles, old sports injuries, as well as a gentle remedy to clear or prevent common colds and flu. Cupping has received a lot of media attention as the trendy therapy of choice by celebrities in recent years. However, this ancient therapy that has been used for thousands of years in Asia and Europe. It involves the application of heated glass cups that vacuum seal on the skin, which draws stagnant blood and metabolites (such as pain chemicals) to the surface of the body. Many patients express a pleasant feeling of deep relaxation in receiving this gentle but powerful form of treatment.\r\n\r\nServices Offered:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a href=\"/services/acupuncturetcm\">Acupuncture/Chinese Medicine</a></li>\r\n</ul>','Chris Eddy','','publish','open','open','','chris','','','2011-03-29 15:23:15','2011-03-29 05:23:15','',43,'http://www.dynamicbodytherapy.com/?page_id=136',4,'page','',0),(137,1,'2009-10-07 22:44:58','2009-10-07 12:44:58','<span style=\"color: green;\">Acupuncturist / Herb Chinese Med Practitioner / Tuina Practitioner (traditional chinese massage)</span>\nB. App Sc in Human Biology &amp; Traditional Chinese Medicine\nATMS\n\n<span style=\"color: green;\">MONDAY:      1pm - 7pm\nTUESDAY:    1pm - 7pm</span>','Chris Eddy','','inherit','open','open','','136-revision','','','2009-10-07 22:44:58','2009-10-07 12:44:58','',136,'http://www.dynamicbodytherapy.com/uncategorized/136-revision',0,'revision','',0),(138,1,'2009-10-07 22:45:04','2009-10-07 12:45:04','<span style=\"color: green;\">Acupuncturist / Herb Chinese Med Practitioner / Tuina Practitioner (traditional chinese massage)</span>\r\nB. App Sc in Human Biology &amp; Traditional Chinese Medicine\r\nATMS\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color: green;\">MONDAY:      1pm - 7pm\r\nTUESDAY:    1pm - 7pm</span>','Chris Eddy','','inherit','open','open','','136-revision-2','','','2009-10-07 22:45:04','2009-10-07 12:45:04