r\n\r\n<strong>Special Interests in Womenâ€™s Health, Fertility &amp; Children</strong>\r\n\r\nShari has completed post graduate osteopathic studies in obstetrics &amp; gynaecology and the treatment of children and enjoys working with the challenges women may face during pregnancy and motherhood.\r\n\r\n<strong>Pregnancy</strong>\r\n\r\nDuring pregnancy there are many physiological processes that take place and large changes to a womenâ€™s body occur in a relatively short space of time. A hormone called Relaxin softens the ligaments around the joints of the pelvis which is a natural process and assists childbirth. However for some women this process can cause the joints of the pelvis to loosen too much and can result in the pelvis becoming unstable or out of alignment and in a susceptible women can contribute to low back and pelvic pain.\r\n\r\nPost pregnancy there will be pressure on different areas such as the upper back and neck. This may be due to poor posture during breast feeding and incorrect lifting techniques.Â  Osteopathic treatment and corrective muscle re-education can aid in the way the body copes with these pressures.\r\n\r\n<strong>Babies &amp; Children</strong>\r\n\r\nA baby will often communicate there is a problem by being unsettled, irritable or wakeful. Symptoms in a newborn baby to be aware of are:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Colic</li>\r\n	<li>excessive wind</li>\r\n	<li>continuous crying</li>\r\n	<li>difficulty feeding or a preference to feed from one breast</li>\r\n	<li>sleeping difficulties</li>\r\n	<li>stiffness of the neck muscles</li>\r\n	<li>favouring the head to one side</li>\r\n	<li>a misshapen head</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nBiodynamic/Cranial Osteopathy can be useful in treating a wide range of symptoms and conditions in children including the following\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>back and neck pain</li>\r\n	<li>ear infections and glue ear</li>\r\n	<li>growing pains</li>\r\n	<li>headaches</li>\r\n	<li>behavioural problems</li>\r\n	<li>hyperactivity</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nspeech problems\r\n\r\nServices Offered:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Read About Osteopathy\" href=\"/services/osteopathy\">Osteopathy</a></li>\r\n</ul>','Shari Trimble','','inherit','open','open','','45-revision-10','','','2009-10-17 17:52:28','2009-10-17 07:52:28','',45,'http://www.dynamicbodytherapy.com/uncategorized/45-revision-10',0,'revision','',0),(173,1,'2009-10-17 17:54:17','2009-10-17 07:54:17','<img class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-176\" src=\"http://www.dynamicbodytherapy.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/10/sarah.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"232\" height=\"251\" />profile coming soon...','Sarah Valentini','','draft','open','open','','sarah-valentini','','','2011-03-10 19:51:45','2011-03-10 09:51:45','',43,'http://www.dynamicbodytherapy.com/?page_id=173',3,'page','',0),(174,1,'2009-10-17 17:54:06','2009-10-17 07:54:06','','Sarah Valentini','','inherit','open','open','','173-revision','','','2009-10-17 17:54:06','2009-10-17 07:54:06','',173,'http://www.dynamicbodytherapy.com/uncategorized/173-revision',0,'revision','',0),(175,1,'2009-10-17 17:54:17','2009-10-17 07:54:17','profile coming soon...','Sarah Valentini','','inherit','open','open','','173-revision-2','','','2009-10-17 17:54:17','2009-10-17 07:54:17','',173,'http://www.dynamicbodytherapy.com/uncategorized/173-revision-2',0,'revision','',0),(176,1,'2009-10-17 17:55:54','2009-10-17 07:55:54','','sarah','','inherit','open','open','','sarah','','','2009-10-17 17:55:54','2009-10-17 07:55:54','',173,'http://www.dynamicbodytherapy.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/10/sarah.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(177,1,'2009-10-17 17:54:57','2009-10-17 07:54:57','profile coming soon...','Sarah Valentini','','inherit','open','open','','173-revision-3','','','2009-10-17 17:54:57','2009-10-17 07:54:57','',173,'http://www.dynamicbodytherapy.com/uncategorized/173-revision-3',0,'revision','',0),(178,1,'2009-10-06 23:32:33','2009-10-06 13:32:33','Dip.H.Sc. in Remedial Therapy\r\nDip. Anatomy, Physiology & Massage [London]\r\nITEC Dip Massage [London]\r\nAAMT, ANTA, AKA (student member), Network Fitness\r\n\r\nWEDNESDAY 12pm - 7:15pm\r\nTHURSDAY 12pm - 7:15pm\r\nFRIDAY 12pm - 7:15pm ','Camille de Niese','','inherit','open','open','','62-revision-4','','','2009-10-06 23:32:33','2009-10-06 13:32:33','',62,'http://www.dynamicbodytherapy.com/uncategorized/62-revision-4',0,'revision','',0),(179,1,'2011-03-29 15:29:31','2011-03-29 05:29:31','Bachelor of Arts Degree\nDip.H.Sc. in Remedial Therapy\nDip of Kinesiology\nDip. Anatomy, Physiology &amp; Massage [London]\nITEC Dip Massage [London]\nAAMT, ANTA, AKA (associate member)\n\nTUESDAY 10am - 7pm\nWEDNESDAY 12pm - 5pm\nTHURSDAY 10am - 7pm\nFRIDAY 12pm - 7pm\n\nCamille has a background in dance (ballet, contemporary &amp; African dance) and sport (netball) and understands the difficulty in overcoming injuries while still being able to keep up with ones physical and lifestyle pursuits.Â  It is this background and her own struggles with injury that lead to Camille becoming a physical therapist.\n\nCamille de Niese has been working in the field of manual therapy for 13 years and has attained qualifications and skills in remedial therapy, massage, kinesiology, manual lymphatic drainage, cupping, neurostructural integration, reiki and pilates instruction.\n\nHaving worked primarily in the structural field of therapy Camille has seen first hand the extent to which our emotions and stress levels impact on us physically causing pain, stiffness and ill health.Â  Often a purely physical approach to treatment is limited and achieving a full and lasting recovery is prolonged due to not fully resolving the primary cause of ill health.Â  This realisation resulted in Camille undertaking further study in Kinesiology which looks at our emotional, energetic, spiritual and physical health.\n\nRemedial Kinesiology is Camille\'s combination of remedial therapy and kinesiology to provide the client with a treatment that deals with the physical, emotional, energetic and spiritual blocks to good health and well being.Â  Through the use of kinesiology Camille is able to determine the priority issue to be dealt with in any given session and works toward restoring balance on all levels.\n\nCamille offers a variety of single therapy treatments including deep tissue massage, remedial therapy, lymphatic drainage and kinesiology as well as remedial kinesiology which provides a truly holistic treatment plan for those clients seeking to work towards resolving more long standing physical and emotional negative patterns, by incorporating a variety of therapies, treatment techniques and rehab exercises to resolve dysfunction at the root cause not just treat the symptoms.','Camille de Niese','','inherit','open','open','','62-autosave','','','2011-03-29 15:29:31','2011-03-29 05:29:31','',62,'http://www.dynamicbodytherapy.com/uncategorized/62-autosave',0,'revision','',0),(180,1,'2009-10-17 17:44:17','2009-10-17 07:44:17','[caption id=\"attachment_103\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"391\" caption=\"Dr Shari Trimble\"]<a href=\"/practitioners/shari\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-103\" title=\"Dr Shari Trimble\" src=\"http://www.dynamicbodytherapy.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/10/shari.jpg\" alt=\"Dr Shari Trimble\" width=\"391\" height=\"503\" /></a>[/caption]','Practioners','','inherit','open','open','','43-revision-5','','','2009-10-17 17:44:17','2009-10-17 07:44:17','',43,'http://www.dynamicbodytherapy.com/uncategorized/43-revision-5',0,'revision','',0),(181,1,'2009-10-17 17:56:22','2009-10-17 07:56:22','<img class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-176\" src=\"http://www.dynamicbodytherapy.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/10/sarah.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"232\" height=\"251\" />profile coming soon...','Sarah Valentini','','inherit','open','open','','173-revision-4','','','2009-10-17 17:56:22','2009-10-17 07:56:22','',173,'http://www.dynamicbodytherapy.com/uncategorized/173-revision-4',0,'revision','',0),(182,1,'2009-10-17 18:04:07','2009-10-17 08:04:07','<img class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-310\" title=\"Anna-Mai\" src=\"http://www.dynamicbodytherapy.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/10/Anna-Mai-website2.JPG\" alt=\"Anna-Mai\" width=\"234\" height=\"351\" />MONDAY 2pm-5:30pm\r\nTUESDAY 2pm-8pm\r\n<h3>Background</h3>\r\nAnna-Mai Hoek graduated the Australian College of Natural Medicine in 2007 with a Diploma in Remedial Therapy and has been a valued practitioner of Dynamic Body Therapy since this time. Anna-Maiâ€™s friendly, enthusiastic nature, skill, knowledge, and experience combined with a genuine desire to help others ensures her clients are always well looked after and come away from her treatments uplifted, relieved and restored. Anna-Mai also teaches massage at Endeavour College of Natural Health in Melbourneâ€™s CBD.\r\n<h3>What is Remedial Therapy?</h3>\r\nRemedial therapy is commonly understood by most to be a form of deep tissue massage to relieve aches and pains. While this is true, remedial therapy applied by a skilled practitioner encompasses a wide range of direct and indirect techniques to â€œremedyâ€ the physical ailments of the body to relieve muscle tension, pain and imbalance, improve circulation, joint range of motion and soft tissue health and function.\r\n<h3>Treatment may include:</h3>\r\nOrthopaedic testing\r\n\r\nMyofascial release\r\n\r\nMuscle energy technique\r\n\r\nLymphatic drainage\r\n\r\nDeep tissue massage/manipulation\r\n\r\nSports injury massage/management\r\n\r\nTrigger point therapy\r\n\r\nRelaxation massage/techniques\r\n\r\nPositional Release\r\n\r\nGentle mobilisation of structures\r\n\r\nMyofascial cupping\r\n\r\nStretch/Strengthening prescription\r\n<h3>Therapist Goal</h3>\r\nAnna-Mai specialises in chronic pain and injury management.Â  Her goal is to restore the function of the soft tissues of the body and address physical imbalance and tension that may be causing pain or discomfort to the client.Â  These may arise from poor posture, injury, overuse, musculoskeletal imbalance and damaging activities of daily living.Â  Her belief is that the soft tissues of the body must be treated as a series of interconnected parts that all interrelate and affect each other and not as a singular structure.Â  Anna-Maiâ€™s goal is not only to treat a symptom or dysfunction, but to identify the cause so as to decrease its impact on the client or eradicate the problem altogether.\r\n<h3>Individually Structured Treatment</h3>\r\nEach client is viewed as an individual with individual needs.Â  Treatment is formulated based on consultation, health history, observation, palpation and if indicated, orthopaedic testing.Â  Treatment undertaken is specific, aiming to address the clientâ€™s direct needs, wishes and expected outcomes.\r\n<h3>Take Home</h3>\r\nAs a remedial therapist Anna-Mai encourages her clients to view their massage treatment as a key component in maintaining their overall health and wellbeing.Â  Anna-Mai will treat musculoskeletal imbalance and soft-tissue dysfunction during a session however, outside the treatment room Anna-Mai encourages her clients to take a proactive approach to their health by leading a healthy lifestyle to nourish both body and mind. \' If we feel vital, fit, energised and pain free, our minds often follow suit\'.Â  Prescriptive stretching or strengthening exercises may be given to clients to enhanceÂ  results.Â  If advice is followed, the client may then be able to reap the full benefits of this holistic approach.\r\n\r\nServices Offered:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a href=\"/services/remedial-massage\">Remedial Massage Therapy</a></li>\r\n	<li>Relaxation Massage</li>\r\n</ul>','Anna-Mai Hoek','','publish','open','open','','anna-mai-hoek','','','2011-03-29 15:36:16','2011-03-29 05:36:16','',43,'http://www.dynamicbodytherapy.com/?page_id=182',5,'page','',0),(183,1,'2009-10-17 18:03:31','2009-10-17 08:03:31','','Anna-Mai Hoek','','inherit','open','open','','182-revision','','','2009-10-17 18:03:31','2009-10-17 08:03:31','',182,'http://www.dynamicbodytherapy.com/uncategorized/182-revision',0,'revision','',0),(184,1,'2009-10-17 18:04:07','2009-10-17 08:04:07','','Anna-Mai Hoek','','inherit','open','open','','182-revision-2','','','2009-10-17 18:04:07','2009-10-17 08:04:07','',182,'http://www.dynamicbodytherapy.com/uncategorized/182-revision-2',0,'revision','',0),(320,1,'2009-10-17 20:27:09','2009-10-17 10:27:09','<h3><strong>What is osteopathy? </strong></h3>\r\nOsteopathy is a holistic based treatment using the hands to correct tissue &amp; joint abnormalities. It is aimed at restoring physical &amp; mental wellbeing and thereby making it easier for the body to use its own recuperative powers to heal itself. The treatment goal is to improve circulation, reduce muscle spasm, improve flexibility, maintain nerve supply &amp; restore muscle/joint harmony\r\n<h3><strong>What kinds of problems can osteopathy help with? </strong></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Lower back pain, neck pain, &amp; other joint complaints</li>\r\n	<li>Headaches and migraines</li>\r\n	<li>Arthritic conditions</li>\r\n	<li>Sporting injuries such as tendonitis and strains, and stress-related muscle pain</li>\r\n	<li>Pregnancy-care for a great pregnancy and labour preparation</li>\r\n	<li>Treatment of babies and children</li>\r\n	<li>Digestive complaints such as reflux, constipation, IBS</li>\r\n	<li>Asthma and other breathing difficulties</li>\r\n	<li>And many more</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><strong>How does osteopathy work? </strong></h3>\r\n<h4>Manipulative Osteopathy</h4>\r\nIs a â€˜whole bodyâ€™ system of manual medicine, based on unique biomechanical principles. The osteopath uses a wide range of techniques such as\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Massage and stretching techniques</li>\r\n	<li>Articulation techniques, in which joints are mobilised by being passively taken through their range of motion</li>\r\n	<li>Muscle Energy techniques, in which contracted muscles are released by alternately being stretched and made to work against resistance.</li>\r\n	<li>Positional Release Techniques, which achieve release of restriction by placing the affected joint or muscle in a position of comfort, while applying a stretching release to the opposing muscles.</li>\r\n	<li>Functional techniques, which involve gentle mobilisation of joints in a way which \"nudges\" barriers to normal movement until a way is found through the restriction</li>\r\n	<li>Manipulation, which may be used where it is appropriate and safe to do so, though it is not the mainstay of most Osteopathic treatments. Osteopathic manipulations are carried out using minimum force levels in order to maximise safety and minimise patient discomfort</li>\r\n	<li>Visceral techniques are used in the management of conditions affecting internal organs. These involve gentle and rhythmical stretching of the visceral areas</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4><strong>Biodynamic Osteopathy</strong></h4>\r\nBiodynamic osteopaths are trained to feel a very subtle, rhythmical change that is present in all body tissues. Known as primary respiratory motion, this intuitive force is capable of restoring health in the patient. Through disciplined study and a refined sense of touch, the Osteopath is able to sense and cooperate with the intention of these forces to promote healing in the patient.<a href=\"/services/biodynamic-cranial-osteopathy\"> read more</a>\r\n<h3><strong>What can I expect when I visit an osteopath? </strong></h3>\r\nWhen you visit an osteopath for the first time a full case history will be taken and you will be taken through a physical examination. You will normally be asked to remove some of your clothing and to perform a simple series of movements. The osteopath will then use a highly developed sense of touch to identify any areas of tension, weakness or altered movement throughout the body.\r\n\r\nThe osteopath may need to request additional investigations such as x-ray or blood tests. This will allow a full diagnosis and suitable treatment plan to be developed for you.\r\n<h3><strong>Can I have osteopathy on my private medical insurance or Medicare? </strong></h3>\r\nMany private health insurance schemes give benefit for osteopathic treatment. Some companies will reimburse the total fee or pay a percentage of the costs. Contact your insurance company who will explain the actual benefits and methods of claim for your individual policy. Our clinic has HICAPS which allows for claims to be made on the spot.\r\n\r\nIf you are claiming your treatment on Medicare as part of an Extended Primary Care (EPC) scheme you must have the relevant documentation from your GP prior to your first visit.\r\n\r\nStaff:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Shari Trimble\" href=\"/practitioners/shari\">Dr Shari Trimble</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"/practitioners/paul\">Dr Paul Turner</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"/practitioners/annabel\">Dr Annabel Eastham</a></li>\r\n</ul>','Osteopathy','','inherit','open','open','','7-revision-20','','','2009-10-17 20:27:09','2009-10-17 10:27:09','',7,'http://www.dynamicbodytherapy.com/uncategorized/7-revision-20',0,'revision','',0),(188,1,'2009-10-17 18:05:43','2009-10-17 08:05:43','<img class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-315\" title=\"Paul Turner\" src=\"http://www.dynamicbodytherapy.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/10/Paul-website.JPG\" alt=\"Paul Turner\" width=\"272\" height=\"407\" />Dr Paul Turner\r\nRegistered Osteopath, Biodynamic Craniosacral Osteopath,\r\nB.App.Sc.(Osteopathy), Member of the A.O.A\r\n\r\nMONDAY 8am â€“ 1pm\r\nSATURDAY 9am â€“ 1pm\r\n\r\nPaul has had over 15 years of experience in Cranio-sacral and Biodynamic Osteopathy as well as multi-dimensional healing methods.Â  This form of healing work is gentle and effective in recovery from dys-function and in improving overall health and well being.\r\n\r\nCommon problems responding well to this form of treatment include:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Difficulties      throughout pregnancy</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li> Infants      and children with a wide range of problems such as colic, reflux,      hyperactivity, some behavioral troubles and pain</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li> Any      acute or chronic pattern of pain</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li> Headaches</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li> Whiplash</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li> Sporting      and work related injuries</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nBecause all aspects of being are addressed, this type of work can compliment other modalities of treatment by providing support in recovery from general life stresses, fatigue and some organ system dysfunctions such as irritable bowel, asthma, insomnia, menstrual pain, lymphatic congestion, etc.\r\n\r\nAs treatment is only one component of the healing process, Paul will also help you to learn effective methods of self healing and rehabilitation. Â This enables you to develop a deeper awareness about your own being and learn how to raise your own level of health.Â  It also helps to avoid unnecessary repetitive visits to therapists for treatment.\r\n\r\nBecause Paul gets you involved in your own healing process, and supports the bodyâ€™s self healing mechanisms in treatment, good success can be achieved in recovery from conditions that are typically slow or unresponsive to traditional treatment method\r\n\r\nServices Offered:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a href=\"/services/osteopathy\">Osteopathy</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"/services/biodynamic-cranial-osteopathy\">Biodynamic Osteopathy</a></li>\r\n</ul>','Paul Turner','','publish','open','open','','paul-turner','','','2011-02-12 22:57:14','2011-02-12 12:57:14','',43,'http://www.dynamicbodytherapy.com/?page_id=188',7,'page','',0),(189,1,'2009-10-17 18:05:34','2009-10-17 08:05:34','','Paul Turner','','inherit','open','open','','188-revision','','','2009-10-17 18:05:34','2009-10-17 08:05:34','',188,'http://www.dynamicbodytherapy.com/uncategorized/188-revision',0,'revision','',0),(190,1,'2009-10-17 18:05:43','2009-10-17 08:05:43','','Paul Turner','','inherit','open','open','','188-revision-2','','','2009-10-17 18:05:43','2009-10