emedyâ€ the physical ailments of the body to relieve muscle tension, pain and imbalance, improve circulation, joint range of motion and soft tissue health and function.\r\n<h3>Treatment may include:</h3>\r\nOrthopaedic testing\r\n\r\nMyofascial release\r\n\r\nMuscle energy technique\r\n\r\nLymphatic drainage\r\n\r\nDeep tissue massage/manipulation\r\n\r\nSports injury massage/management\r\n\r\nTrigger point therapy\r\n\r\nRelaxation massage/techniques\r\n\r\nPositional Release\r\n\r\nGentle mobilisation of structures\r\n\r\nMyofascial cupping\r\n\r\nStretch/Strengthening prescription\r\n<h3>Therapist Goal</h3>\r\nAnna-Mai specialises in chronic pain and injury management.Â  Her goal is to restore the function of the soft tissues of the body and address physical imbalance and tension that may be causing pain or discomfort to the client.Â  These may arise from poor posture, injury, overuse, musculoskeletal imbalance and damaging activities of daily living.Â  Her belief is that the soft tissues of the body must be treated as a series of interconnected parts that all interrelate and affect each other and not as a singular structure.Â  Anna-Maiâ€™s goal is not only to treat a symptom or dysfunction, but to identify the cause so as to decrease its impact on the client or eradicate the problem altogether.\r\n<h3>Individually Structured Treatment</h3>\r\nEach client is viewed as an individual with individual needs.Â  Treatment is formulated based on consultation, health history, observation, palpation and if indicated, orthopaedic testing.Â  Treatment undertaken is specific, aiming to address the clientâ€™s direct needs, wishes and expected outcomes.\r\n<h3>Take Home</h3>\r\nAs a remedial therapist Anna-Mai encourages her clients to view their massage treatment as a key component in maintaining their overall health and wellbeing.Â  Anna-Mai will treat musculoskeletal imbalance and soft-tissue dysfunction during a session however, outside the treatment room Anna-Mai encourages her clients to take a proactive approach to their health by leading a healthy lifestyle to nourish both body and mind. \' If we feel vital, fit, energised and pain free, our minds often follow suit\'.Â  Prescriptive stretching or strengthening exercises may be given to clients to enhanceÂ  results.Â  If advice is followed, the client may then be able to reap the full benefits of this holistic approach.\r\n\r\nServices Offered:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a href=\"/services/remedial-massage\">Remedial Massage Therapy</a></li>\r\n</ul>','Anna-Mai Hoek','','inherit','open','open','','182-revision-9','','','2011-03-29 15:34:49','2011-03-29 05:34:49','',182,'http://www.dynamicbodytherapy.com/uncategorized/182-revision-9',0,'revision','',0),(375,1,'2010-02-20 19:18:44','2010-02-20 09:18:44','<strong><img class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-303\" title=\"Dr Chris Eddy\" src=\"http://www.dynamicbodytherapy.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/10/Chris-website.JPG\" alt=\"Dr Chris Eddy\" width=\"239\" height=\"359\" />Dr Chris Eddy</strong>\r\n<strong>Traditional Chinese medicine</strong>\r\n<strong>Ba.App.Sci TCM &amp; HB</strong>\r\n<strong>RMIT, Melb. NUTCM, Nanjing.\r\n</strong>\r\n\r\nMONDAY 1pm-7pm\r\nTUESDAY 10am-6pm<strong> </strong>\r\n\r\n<strong> </strong>\r\n\r\n<strong> </strong>\r\n<h3><strong>Dr. Chris Eddy is a Registered Chinese Medicine Practitioner.</strong></h3>\r\nDr Eddy offers a professional and effective service providing each of his patients with warmth, care and compassion.\r\n\r\nChris graduated from RMIT University holding a double science degree in Chinese Medicine &amp; Human Biology. Â  Following this he pursued his studies completing a clinical internship at Jiangsu Provincial Hospital in China, and returning for a further year of study in Nanjing in the acupuncture department of Nanjing Western hospital. Â  Dr Eddy extensively researches male health and fertility issues, keeping up to date with latest treatment options and integrating traditional Chinese medicine treatment and knowledge with modern research. â€˜The best medicine is the one that worksâ€™.\r\n<h3><strong>Chris has a special interest in the treatment of Male Fertility and General Health, Digestive problems, Sports injuries &amp; Chronic Pain Disorders.</strong></h3>\r\n<strong> </strong>\r\n\r\nDr Eddy applies extensive knowledge of anatomy and physiology by effectively integrating it into his practice of Natural Medicine. Â Different modalities are combined including Acupuncture, Herbal Medicine, Nutrition &amp; Massage Therapy in order to provide for you a safe, effective and natural treatment, healing both the mind and body.Â  It is ensured that our Patients are active participants in their own good health and that together they work out a treatment plan that provides the best possible outcome.\r\n<strong> </strong>\r\n<h3><strong>Therapy</strong></h3>\r\nChris practices traditional Chinese medicine which includes therapies of acupuncture, cupping, herbal medicine and massage. Chinese medicine treats a very wide range of ailments; however a lot of Chrisâ€™s time is focused on treating male health &amp; fertility, chronic pain and digestive disorders.\r\nJapanese and Chinese Style Acupuncture\r\n\r\nAcupuncture does not need to be painful to be effective. Dr Eddy has studied various styles of acupuncture including Chinese, Japanese and more western approaches, with the aim to offer his patients the best therapeutic outcome. The Japanese style uses disposable needles of very fine gauge, which means little or no pain upon insertion.\r\n<h3>Chinese Herbal Medicine</h3>\r\nDr Eddy tailors each formula specifically to his patientsâ€™ individual health and lifestyle needs. Some raw herb formulas may not have the best taste, but they have been proven over thousands of years to help our bodies heal themselves. Dr Eddy often offers his patientsâ€™ a choice of raw &amp; granulated herbs as an integral part of their treatment. Sometimes herbal pills are prescribed in conjunction with the patient\'s raw herbs when traveling or boiling preparation may be inconvenient.\r\n<h3><strong>Cupping</strong></h3>\r\nDr Eddy has used Cupping Therapy effectively to help heal chronically sore muscles, old sports injuries, as well as a gentle remedy to clear or prevent common colds and flu. Cupping has received a lot of media attention as the trendy therapy of choice by celebrities in recent years. However, this ancient therapy that has been used for thousands of years in Asia and Europe. It involves the application of heated glass cups that vacuum seal on the skin, which draws stagnant blood and metabolites (such as pain chemicals) to the surface of the body. Many patients express a pleasant feeling of deep relaxation in receiving this gentle but powerful form of treatment.\r\n\r\nServices Offered:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a href=\"/services/acupuncturetcm\">Acupuncture/Chinese Medicine</a></li>\r\n</ul>','Chris Eddy','','inherit','open','open','','136-revision-13','','','2010-02-20 19:18:44','2010-02-20 09:18:44','',136,'http://www.dynamicbodytherapy.com/uncategorized/136-revision-13',0,'revision','',0),(376,1,'2010-02-20 18:39:31','2010-02-20 08:39:31','Dip.H.Sc. in Remedial Therapy\r\nDip. Anatomy, Physiology &amp; Massage [London]\r\nITEC Dip Massage [London]\r\nAAMT, ANTA, AKA (student member), Network Fitness\r\n\r\nWEDNESDAY 12pm - 7:15pm\r\nTHURSDAY 12pm - 7:15pm\r\nFRIDAY 12pm - 7:15pm\r\n\r\nCamille has a background in dance (ballet, contemporary &amp; African dance) and sport (netball) and understands the difficulty in overcoming injuries while still being able to keep up with ones physical and lifestyle pursuits.Â  It is this background and her own struggles with injury that lead to Camille becoming a physical therapist.\r\n\r\nCamille de Niese has been working in the field of manual therapy for 13 years and has attained qualifications and skills in remedial therapy, massage, kinesiology, manual lymphatic drainage, cupping, neurostr